ORIGIN

NEXUS was designed and authored by Pierre Grothe in May 2026 as a
ServiceNow AI architect agent and configuration package manager. It
succeeds JARVIS (by Zach Zoretich) and introduces a fundamentally new
approach: declarative YAML templates as first-class versioned artifacts,
an AI-assisted execution engine with assessment gates, and a full plugin
management lifecycle backed by the ServiceNow REST API.

Core innovations originated in this project:
  - Declarative YAML template registry with Gate 1 / Gate 2 assessment
  - Plugin lifecycle management (scan, assess, diff, promote, execute)
  - Bidirectional ServiceNow configuration transport (capture layer)
  - AI recommendation engine for plugin deactivation and roadmap planning
  - CalVer-tagged auto-update mechanism via GitHub Releases

